Commentary: is that the game? It's another lovely display of defensive, but attacking spin bowling. He knows Shadab is going to come so he tosses it up, but wide outside off. Shadab runs down, looking to hit the ball over cover. Instead, it skews off the outside half to short third man. Just like how de Grandhomme got out to Chahal in the second ODI in Pune last year. It's a defensive attacking option, oxymoron-ish as it may be
Commentary_short: Santner to Shadab Khan, OUT
Dismissal_text: Shadab Khan c Nicholls b Santner 54 (93m 77b 5x4 0x6) SR: 70.12

Commentary: and that's the game. It doesn't go to the last over, but that was a sensational finish to the ODI series. A short slower delivery outside off, Raees swats it away towards midwicket, who keeps his eyes on the ball and takes a reverse-cupped catch. New Zealand complete a 5-0 sweep in the ODIs
